ABOUT AAS

Agriculture is the science and art of cultivating plants and livestock. Agriculture was the key development in the rise of sedentary human civilization, whereby farming of domesticated species created food surpluses that enabled people to live in cities. Aquaculture (less commonly spelled aquiculture), also known as aqua farming, is the farming of fish, crustaceans, mollusks, aquatic plants, algae, and other organisms. Aquaculture involves cultivating freshwater and saltwater populations under controlled conditions; and can be contrasted with commercial fishing, which is the harvesting of wild fish. Mariculture commonly known as marine farming refers to aquaculture practiced in marine environments and in underwater habitats, as opposed to in freshwater. Particular kind of aquaculture includes fish farming, shrimp farming, oyster farming, mariculture, alga culture (such as seaweed farming), and the cultivation of ornamental fish.

KLEF has been awarded the Highest-grade A++ by NAAC. It has been approved by the All-India Council for Technical Education, New Delhi.

KLEF strives to provide plenty of opportunities to explore their talents and interests for students of international background, a thriving community of creative and accomplished people from across the globe.

SURABHI 2021

SURABHI 2021 is an International Cultural Fest, held virtually involving over 6 continents and will give out 30,000 + registrations for the fest.

SURABHI 2021 is held in collaboration with Jignasa, an Organization that promotes Entrepreneurship in Culture, Fine Arts, Heritage, Literature through promoting Life Skill Development and Creative Leadership with Education initiatives and activities.

The Goal of Surabhi is to excite people and create a joyful environment for all age groups and events for them to participate discover their talents or improve them and relieve people of the stress they face normally in the outside world and this year we have decided on the theme would be about the independence we got because of many struggles and lives of freedom fighters to achieve it for us.

This year it's following the theme AZAADI KA AMRUTH MAHOTSAV which is in the memory of the Indians who struggled for independence and the freedom fighters who gave their life up for our freedom.

THEME OF SURABHI 2021

‘Independence’ the word itself sounds so soothing and makes us recall the tears, struggles, fights and victories of our country. It’s been 75 years since our nation felt its first bliss of freedom.

With regards to that glorious victory, our honourable prime minister made a call of “AZAADI KA AMRUTH MAHOTSAV” to recall and adore those who fought for us and in response to hon’ble prime minister’s call, KLU is planning and heading to make ‘SURABHI 2021’ a big and grand success

CULTIVATION OF CROPS

Cultivation of crops often first involves tilling (or plowing) the land. (A machine that does this is called a cultivator). It also involves planting seeds and then watering them and making sure they are growing properly. When crops and plants are cultivated, they are taken care of until they are ready to be harvested.

During these tough times, Surabhi 2020 came with the brilliant idea of conducting the fest in online mode and made it the largest international cultural fest in the country. Surabhi consists of various events like speaking, literature, Dance, Dramatics, Music, Quizzes, Arts & Crafts, Fashion & Lifestyle, and Surabhi Specials with a total of 40 events. We have a total of 23000+ registrations, with participation of students in all the events from various colleges from all over India.
